law.text:
In a consolidation, merger, or share exchange, stock in a corporation may be exchanged for or converted into and, in a transfer of assets, assets may be transferred in consideration of any one or more of the following:
Stock, evidence of indebtedness, partnership or limited liability company interests, or other securities of the successor or any other corporation or entity, whether or not a party to the transaction;
Other tangible or intangible property;
Money; and
Any other consideration.
